
Step1:
Create a file.sh (test_crontab.sh)
add some command to be run in it

step2:
on the terminal do:
crontab -e : to create task schedule in crontab file

m h  dom mon dow   command
1 * * * * bash /home/cesar/Desktop/test_crontab.sh    (runs every one minutes)
52 0 20 * * bash /home/cesar/Desktop/test_crontab.sh 




 Crontab Commands

export EDITOR=vi ;to specify a editor to open crontab file.

crontab -e    Edit crontab file, or create one if it doesnâ€™t already exist.
crontab -l    crontab list of cronjobs , display crontab file contents.
crontab -r    Remove your crontab file.
crontab -v    Display the last time you edited your crontab file. (This option is only available on a few systems.)

